TITLE      The cross sections of the proton nuclear reactions on
            Cd isotopes
AUTHOR     (J.-D.An, C.-J.Kim, H.-S.Jin, M.-S.Go)
INSTITUTE  (3KDRKDR) Kim Il Sung University, Pyongyang
REFERENCE  (J,RED,170,901,2015)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,3KDRPYN) MGC-20 cyclotron of Institute of Atomic
            Energy, Pyongyang
SAMPLE     The target stack used 17 cadmium foils (10-20 mg/cm2,
            99.9% purity) and 18 copper foils (21.4 mg/cm2,
            99.99% purity), arranged alternately.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) 100 cm3
METHOD     (ACTIV,BCINT) Proton beam flux determined with a
            Faraday cup and current integrator.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Total uncertainties are due to:
           (ERR-1,,0.1) Foil thickness (<0.1%)
           (ERR-2,,6.) Counting efficiency of gamma-spectrometer
            (<6%)
           (ERR-3,,8.) Radioactivity  (<8%)
           (ERR-4,,3.) Proton beam current (<3%)
STATUS     (TABLE,,J.-D.An+,J,RED,170,901,2015) Table 1
HISTORY    (20260303C) VT
